<p><b>4. How We Use Your Data</b></p>
<p>We process your personal data for the following purposes:</p>
<ul>
  <li><b>Order fulfillment: </b>to process, ship, and deliver your orders for plant fertilizers and related products</li>
  <li><b>Account management: </b>to create and manage your customer account</li>
  <li><b>Payment processing: </b>to process payments through our payment service providers</li>
  <li><b>Customer communication: </b>to respond to inquiries, send order confirmations, shipping updates, and delivery notifications</li>
  <li><b>Legal obligations: </b>to comply with tax, accounting, and other legal requirements</li>
  <li><b>Fraud prevention: </b>to detect and prevent fraudulent transactions</li>
  <li><b>Marketing: </b>to send promotional communications about our products (only with your explicit consent)</li>
  <li><b>Website improvement: </b>to analyze website usage and improve our E-shop experience</li>
</ul>
<p><b>4.1 Legal Basis for Processing</b></p>
<ul>
  <li><b>Contract performance (Art. 6(1)(b)): </b>processing your orders and managing your account</li>
  <li><b>Legal obligation (Art. 6(1)(c)): </b>tax records, accounting, and invoicing requirements</li>
  <li><b>Consent (Art. 6(1)(a)): </b>marketing communications and non-essential cookies. You may withdraw consent at any time.</li>
  <li><b>Legitimate interests (Art. 6(1)(f)): </b>fraud prevention, website analytics, and service improvement</li>
</ul>
<p><b>5. Third-Party Services and Data Sharing</b></p>
<p>We may share your data with the following categories of service providers:</p>
<ul>
  <li><b>Payment processors: </b>to securely process your payments. We do not store full payment card details.</li>
  <li><b>Shipping and logistics providers: </b>to deliver your orders (name, shipping address, phone number)</li>
  <li><b>Email service providers: </b>to send transactional and marketing emails</li>
  <li><b>Analytics providers: </b>to analyze website traffic and usage patterns (e.g., Google Analytics)</li>
  <li><b>Hosting providers: </b>to host our E-shop infrastructure</li>
</ul>
<p>We do not sell your personal data to any third party. All service providers are bound by data processing agreements in compliance with the GDPR.</p>
<p><b>6. International Data Transfers</b></p>
<p>Some of our service providers may process data outside the European Economic Area (EEA). Where this occurs, we ensure appropriate safeguards such as Standard Contractual Clauses approved by the European Commission are in place.</p>
<p><b>7. Data Retention</b></p>
<p>We retain your personal data for the following periods:</p>
<ul>
  <li><b>Account data: </b>for the duration of your account, plus 30 days after deletion</li>
  <li><b>Order and transaction data: </b>for 10 years as required by Slovak tax and accounting legislation</li>
  <li><b>Marketing consent records: </b>for the duration of your consent, plus 1 year after withdrawal</li>
  <li><b>Website analytics data: </b>up to 26 months</li>
  <li><b>Customer support correspondence: </b>for 3 years after the last interaction</li>
</ul>
<p><b>8. Data Security</b></p>
<p>We implement appropriate technical and organizational measures to protect your personal data, including encrypted connections (HTTPS/TLS), secure payment processing, restricted access controls, and regular security assessments.</p>
<p><b>9. Cookies and Tracking Technologies</b></p>
<p>Our E-shop uses cookies and similar technologies:</p>
<ul>
  <li><b>Essential cookies: </b>required for the E-shop to function (cart, session, authentication). These cannot be disabled.</li>
  <li><b>Analytics cookies: </b>to understand how visitors interact with our website (e.g., Google Analytics). Placed only with your consent.</li>
  <li><b>Marketing cookies: </b>to deliver relevant advertisements. Placed only with your consent.</li>
</ul>
<p>You can manage your cookie preferences through the cookie consent banner displayed on your first visit, or through your browser settings at any time.</p>
<p><b>10. Your Rights Under the GDPR</b></p>
<p>As a data subject, you have the following rights:</p>
<ul>
  <li><b>Right of access (Art. 15): </b>obtain a copy of your personal data we hold</li>
  <li><b>Right to rectification (Art. 16): </b>correct inaccurate or incomplete data</li>
  <li><b>Right to erasure (Art. 17): </b>request deletion of your personal data</li>
  <li><b>Right to restriction (Art. 18): </b>restrict processing in certain circumstances</li>
  <li><b>Right to data portability (Art. 20): </b>receive your data in a machine-readable format</li>
  <li><b>Right to object (Art. 21): </b>object to processing based on legitimate interests or direct marketing</li>
  <li><b>Right to withdraw consent: </b>withdraw consent at any time without affecting prior processing</li>
</ul>
<p>To exercise your rights, contact us at privacy@gardenyx.eu. We will respond within 30 days. You also have the right to lodge a complaint with the Office for Personal Data Protection of the Slovak Republic (Úrad na ochranu osobných údajov SR).</p>
<p><b>11. Children’s Privacy</b></p>
<p>Our E-shop is not directed at children under the age of 16. We do not knowingly collect personal data from children. If you believe a child has provided us with personal data, contact us at privacy@gardenyx.eu.</p>
<p><b>12. Changes to This Privacy Policy</b></p>
<p>We may update this Privacy Policy from time to time. Material changes will be communicated via email or a notice on our website. The "Effective Date" at the top indicates when the latest version became effective.</p>
